### Admin API Testing
### Use REST Client extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@token = YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Login as Admin (Get Token First)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 2. Get Dashboard Statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. Create Product
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "New Product",
  "description": "Product description",
  "price": 99.99,
  "stock": 50,
  "category": "Electronics",
  "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1505740420928-5e560c06d30e?w=500"
}

### 4. Update Product
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/products/PRODUCT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Product Name",
  "price": 89.99,
  "stock": 45
}

### 5. Delete Product
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/admin/products/PRODUCT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Get All Orders (Admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Update Order Status
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/orders/ORDER_ID_HERE/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "shipped"
}

### 8. Get All Users
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Grant Admin Access to User
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/USER_ID_HERE/admin
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "isAdmin": true
}

### 10. Revoke Admin Access
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/USER_ID_HERE/admin
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "isAdmin": false
}

### Test Non-Admin Access (Should Fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/stats
Authorization: Bearer REGULAR_USER_TOKEN_HERE
